4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT REVISING WORKING RETIREE PROVISIONS UNDER THE
5 TEACHERS' RETIREMENT SYSTEM; AMENDING SECTION 19-20-732, MCA; AMENDING SECTION 4,
6 CHAPTER 307, LAWS OF 2019, AND SECTION 4, CHAPTER 135, LAWS OF 2023; AND PROVIDING AN
7 EFFECTIVE DATE AND A TERMINATION DATE.”
8
9 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
10
11 Section 1. Section 19-20-732, MCA, is amended to read:
12 "19-20-732. (Temporary) Reemployment of certain retired teachers, specialists, and
13 administrators -- procedure -- definitions. (1) Subject to the provisions of this section:
14 (a) a teacher, specialist, or administrator who has been receiving a retirement allowance for no
15 less than 2 months, except a disability retirement allowance pursuant to part 9 of this chapter, may be
16 employed on a full-time basis by an employer for a maximum of 3 years 5 years during the lifetime of the retired
17 member without the loss or interruption of any payments or retirement benefits if:
18 (i) the retired member completed 27 or more years of creditable service prior to retirement;
19 (ii) the retired member holds a valid certificate pursuant to the provisions of 20-4-106; and
20 (iii) each year, prior to employing a retired member, the employer certifies to the office of public
21 instruction and to the retirement board that after having advertised the position for that year the employer has
22 been unable to fill the position because the employer either has received no qualified applications or has not
23 received an acceptance of an offer of employment made to a nonretired teacher, specialist, or administrator.
24 The office of public instruction shall verify that the employer has advertised the position as required under this
25 subsection (1)(a)(iii).
26 (b) the employer certification required by this section must include the retired member's name and
27 social security number and a copy of the proposed contract of employment for the retired member;
28 (c) upon receipt of the employer's certification and of the proposed contract of employment, the
